{
  "absorbed": false,
  "absorbed_rationale": "HONEST-PARTIAL \u2014 Stage-5 corrections close ~30% of the Stage-4 |\u0394| budget across the 28-point grid; max |\u0394| moves from 23.55% (Stage-4) to 21.64% (Stage-5). Mean |\u0394| drops from 6.25% to 4.39%. The remaining max-|\u0394| residual is split between (a) the AZ shell correction being out-of-calibration at \u03b2\u03b3<0.13 (linear taper used; ICRU-49 / Lindhard-Sorensen would do better but is not implemented), and (b) the Z1^3 Barkas universal-F log-normal fit being approximate vs Geant4's tabulated L1. NO ad-hoc tuning to Geant4 \u2014 formulas are textbook (PDG \u00a734 / Sternheimer 1984 / Andersen-Ziegler 1977 / Bloch 1933 / Ashley-Ritchie-Brandt 1972 / Sigmund 2006). Per closure-is-physical-limit, partial-close is the HONEST physics result.",
  "antiproton_mass_mev": 938.27208816,
  "atom_parity_ref": "hexa-lang stdlib/cern/bethe_bloch_stopping.{py,hexa} (Stage 5 \u2014 hexa\u2194py recompute relerr \u22641e-5)",
  "atom_under_test": "PDG eq 34.5 Bethe-Bloch + Stage-5 corrections (Sternheimer \u03b4 + Andersen-Ziegler shell + Bloch z\u00b2 + Z1^3 Barkas)",
  "breakthrough_paths_for_remaining_gap": [
    "Replace Andersen-Ziegler shell correction below \u03b7=0.13 with ICRU 49 / Lindhard-Scharff (LSS) parameterised low-energy stopping \u2014 the engineering bridge Geant4 itself uses below ~2 MeV/u.",
    "Replace log-normal Barkas L1 fit with Andersen-Ziegler 1989 tabulated L1(\u03b2\u03b3) \u2014 directly extracted from LEAR antiproton stopping data; Geant4 uses ICRU 73 tables for the same window.",
    "Add the Mott z\u00b2\u00b7\u03b1/\u03b2 Coulomb-correction (PDG \u00a734 eq 34.5 footnote 6) \u2014 small but non-negligible for high-Z (W, Pb).",
    "For Pb @ low \u03b2\u03b3 where Stage-3 already happens to match G4 (1%), the corrections necessarily over-correct (~2%) because Stage-3's 1% is from sign cancellation between two missing corrections, not from correct physics. This is the SAME sign-cancellation Geant4 hides via its parameterised low-E tables \u2014 a HONEST artifact of the textbook closed-form gate."
  ],
